<component name="FlowVis2D" category="Visualization" optional="true">
  <overview>
    <authors>
      <author>Kurt Zimmerman</author>
    </authors>
    <summary> This module takes 2D slice of 3D vector data a applies some standard flow vis algorithms to that data.
    </summary>
    <description>
      <p>The FlowVis2D module is used to visualize slices of 3D vector
        data.  The two inputs are an ImageField/<Vector/> and a
          Colormap. This module requires that pixel and fragment
          programs be available.  The code is substantially faster if
          pbuffer support is available, but will use pixel reads and
          writes if necessary.  To obtain a 2D slice from a 3D vector
          field you can use the <modref package="SCIRun" name="SamplePlane"/> 
          module and the <modref package="SCIRun" name="DirectMapping"/>
          module to obtain a slice from a 3D Vector Field. 
      </p>
    </description>
  </overview>
  <implementation>
  </implementation>
  <io>
    <inputs lastportdynamic="no">
      <port>
	<name>Vector Slice </name>
	<datatype>SCIRun::Field</datatype>
      </port>
      <port>
	<name>ColorMap</name>
	<datatype>SCIRun::ColorMap</datatype>
      </port>
    </inputs>
    <outputs>
      <port>
        <name>Geometry</name>
        <datatype>SCIRun::Geometry</datatype>
      </port>
      <port>
        <name>ColorMap</name>
	<datatype>SCIRun::ColorMap</datatype>
      </port>
    </outputs>
  </io>
  <gui>
  </gui>
  <testing>
  </testing>
</component>
